h3. Issue Summary
Using double quote character “ instead of " on the MDM configuration is not recognized the the Jira mobile app and it reports an misconfiguration on MDM.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Add the following line to the MDM:
{code}
[ 
 {"title": “My Jira Site”, "baseURL": "https://jira.example.com"} ,  
 {"title": “Bug Tracker“, "baseURL": "https://bugs.example.com/jira"} 
]
{code}

 # Try accessing the mobile app. You may need to reinstall it.


h3. Expected Results
The app would recognize both “ and " characters, as in some textfields they even look the same, and some keyboard configurations print “ instead of ".

h3. Actual Results
The app doesn't preload the sites and shows a MDM misconfiguration error.

h3. Workaround
Replace the “ characters for " everywhere on the sites configuration on MDM.
You may need to copy & paste as the characters may look exactly the same on the editor or you keyboard only prints “.
{code}
[ 
 {"title": "My Jira Site", "baseURL": "https://jira.example.com"} ,  
 {"title": "Bug Tracker", "baseURL": "https://bugs.example.com/jira"} 
]
{code}

The following issue's been opened to address [the documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftwareserver/mobile-device-management-mdm-979410052.html] fix: [JRASERVER-72011|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-72011]

h3.Current status
{panel}
The [Mobile Device Management (MDM)|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftwareserver/mobile-device-management-mdm-979410052.html] documentation suggests using the following code for multiple URLs:
{code}
[ 
 {"title": “My Jira Site”, "baseURL": "https://jira.example.com"} ,  
 {"title": “Bug Tracker“, "baseURL": "https://bugs.example.com/jira"} 
]
{code}
Notice how the double quotes character is different on *"*title*"* and *“*My Jira Site*”*.
{panel}

h3.Problem
{panel}
The app won't recognize the *“* character and complain there's a misconfiguration with MDM.
On the MDM page (maybe on some browsers), the two double quote characters look exactly the same.
This misleads the users and have them reach out for support.
{panel}

h3.Suggested fix
{panel}
Simply change the *“* character for *"*.
{panel}

When working on integration tools with the JIRA, it's often useful to be able to display links to issues or comments or other entities that are references from those other tools.

Currently the API returns a url to an entity in the \{{self}} field. This is useful for further API retrievals / references, but it is a url to the REST API returning json.

i.e.

{{"self":"https://jira.host.com/rest/api/2/issue/115254/comment/466578"}}

Where it would be useful to have additionally something like:

{{"permlink":"https://jira.host.com/browse/ISEC-427?focusedCommentId=466576"}}

or 

{\{"display_url":"https://jira.host.com/browse/ISEC-427?focusedCommentId=466576"}}

 

Same for links to Jira issues:

 

{{"permlink":"https://jira.host.com/browse/ISEC-427"}}

 

It is possible to construct these urls ourserlves in our tool. But this add logic / information around Jira display url constructs to our tools.

 
{code:java}
